<h1>Manton Reece</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://manton.org/now">manton.org/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Austin
TX
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Founder of Riverfold Software.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I build iOS apps for search and archiving, co-host the Core Intuition podcast for developers, and write essays and microblog posts at manton.org <<a href="http://manton.org/>.">http://manton.org/>.</a>
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
Publishing on the web is fragile, with important sites and content disappearing every day. I want to build apps that help people record and preserve what matters to them.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Quitting a day job of 14 years is really scary until you do it. Afterwards, it seems like the most natural thing in the world to move on.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
The Martian by Andy Weir.
</p>

